Help

The majority of this report makes use of the R-package, pointblank. pointblank provides tools for validating data. Data validation refers to the act of verifying that the data meets expected requirements. For example, pointblank can verify that all of the expected columns are present and represent the expected data type (e.g., character, integer, logical, etc.). In this report, the results of the validation process are generally reported in tables generated by the pointblank function interogate(). The figure below describes how to interpret these tables.
